Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Lake has some pollen on it- sunny- ripples on surface.
Pollen on lake- partly cloudy- small waves- hard rain last night.
Ripples on surface- little boat traffic.
Breezy- sunny and warm last few days.
Little rain in weeks- windy- much weed growth.
Choppy from jet skis and boat traffic.
Windy- more reeds- lily pads and weeds each year.
Small particles bloom water still in.
Cloudy water with "flecks" floating in it.  Lots of boat traffic over weekend.
Cloudy.  Has been raining for past several days.
Clearest and least weeds to date.
Less tall weeds in some areas- more little ones encroaching to shore.
Cloudy- breezy- very windy- and rainy for five days previous.
Partly cloudy- some chop- and pollen.
Partly cloudy and a slight chop.
Extremely windy and hot - temperature 92 degrees.
Heavy rains earlier in the week.
Calm- a lot of pollen and little clumps of algae  Floating. Weeds at surface already.
Breezy- ripples on lake. Recent rainfall (3 days ago)
Very calm- no boat traffic. Lots of pollen and things floating.
Partly cloudy- boat traffic.  Cloudy water.
Windy- cloudy.  No boat traffic.  Water color: green-brown.
Windy.  Over a week of highs 80-90 F.
A lot of boat chop.  Low wind.  Water color: green-brown
